s used by sttp client and tapir as a shared HTTP modeling layer.</details> |\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/zio_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"sttp-shared zio_3 is the Scala 3 JVM module that adds ZIO stream support to sttp-shared's streaming capability abstraction. It provides the ZioStreams capability, including byte-limit handling for ZStream values used by sttp client, Tapir, and related sttp projects.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.shared/core_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"sttp-shared core provides common Scala abstractions used across the sttp ecosystem, including typed capability markers, attribute maps, monad error typeclasses, and streaming and web socket capability definitions. This artifact is the Scala 3 JVM build of that shared foundation, enabling sttp client, tapir, model, and related modules to express effects, streams, and request and response metadata consistently.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.monovore/decline-effect_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Decline Effect adds Cats Effect integration to the decline command-line parser for Scala. It provides CommandIOApp so applications can define composable CLI parsers with decline and execute commands as cats-effect IO programs.\\\",\\n./metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:5:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/org/typelevel/cats-effect_3/$version$/cats-effect_3-$version$-sources.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:6:    \\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/typelevel/cats-effect\\\",\\n./metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:7:    \\\"test-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/typelevel/cats-effect/tree/v$version$/tests\\\",\\n./metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:8:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/typelevel/cats-effect/tree/v$version$/docs\\\",\\n./metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/index.json:53:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" :