 headers, query parameters, multipart parts, and server-sent events. It includes parsing and serialization helpers for these values and is used by sttp client and tapir as a shared HTTP modeling layer.\\\",\\n./metadata/org.http4s/http4s-ember-server_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"http4s Ember Server is the Ember backend implementation for running http4s servers on the JVM. It provides a lightweight, functional HTTP server for the http4s ecosystem using cats-effect and FS2.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/index.json:5:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/softwaremill/sttp/tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/$version$/tapir-http4s-server_3-$version$-sources.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/index.json:6:    \\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/softwaremill/tapir\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/index.json:7:    \\\"test-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/softwaremill/tapir/tree/v$version$/server/http4s-server/src/test/scala\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/index.json:8:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/softwaremill/sttp/tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/$version$/tapir-http4s-server_3-$version$-javadoc.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Tapir lets Scala developers describe HTTP API endpoints as immutable, reusable values and derive server, client, and OpenAPI integrations from those descriptions. The tapir-http4s-server module interprets Tapir server endpoints as http4s routes for cats-effect applications, including request and response handling, fs2 streaming, server-sent events, and WebSocket support.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-http4s-server_3/index.json:66:      \\\"sttp.tapir.server.http4s\\\"\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-cats-effect_3/index.json:5:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/softwaremill/sttp/tapir/tapir-cats-effect_3/$version$/tapir-cats-effect_3-$version$-sources.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-cats-effect_3/index.json:6:    \\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/softwaremill/tapir\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-cats-effect_3/index.json:8:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo.maven.apache.org/maven2/com/softwaremill/sttp/tapir/tapir-cats-effect_3/$version$/tapir-cats-effect_3-$version$-javadoc.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-cats-effect_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Tapir is a Scala library for describing HTTP API endpoints as immutable, type-safe values and deriving server, client, and OpenAPI, AsyncAPI, or JSON Schema integrations from them. The tapir-cats-effect module provides a Cats Effect Sync-backed MonadError adapter so Tapir interpreters and endpoint logic can run in Cats Effect-based applications.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-cats-effect_3/index.json:18:      \\\"sttp.tapir.integ.cats.effect\\\"\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-zio_3/index.json:5:    \\\"source-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/softwaremill/sttp/tapir/tapir-zio_3/$version$/tapir-zio_3-$version$-sources.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-zio_3/index.json:6:    \\\"repository-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/softwaremill/tapir\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-zio_3/index.json:7:    \\\"test-code-url\\\" : \\\"https://github.com/softwaremill/tapir/tree/v$version$/integrations/zio/src/test\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-zio_3/index.json:8:    \\\"documentation-url\\\" : \\\"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/com/softwaremill/sttp/tapir/tapir-zio_3/$version$/tapir-zio_3-$version$-javadoc.jar\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-zio_3/index.json:9:    \\\"description\\\" : \\\"Tapir is a Scala library for describing HTTP APIs as type-safe endpoints that can be interpreted as servers, clients, and OpenAPI, AsyncAPI, or JSON Schema documentation. The tapir-zio module adds ZIO-specific endpoint helpers, server endpoint types, monad support, and streaming support so Tapir endpoints can be written with ZIO effects.\\\",\\n./metadata/com.softwaremill.sttp.tapir/tapir-zio_3/index.json:18:      \\\"sttp.tapir.ztapir\\\"\\n./stats/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/2.5.1/execution-metrics.json:4:    \\\"library\\\": \\\"org.typelevel:cats-effect_3:2.5.1\\\",\\n./stats/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/2.5.1/execution-metrics.json:52:      \\\"test_file\\\": \\\"tests/src/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/2.5.1/src/test/scala/org_typelevel/cats_effect_3/Cats_effect_3Test.scala\\\",\\n./stats/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/2.5.1/execution-metrics.json:53:      \\\"metadata_file\\\": \\\"metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/2.5.1/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\\n./stats/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/3.1.1/execution-metrics.json:4:    \\\"library\\\": \\\"org.typelevel:cats-effect_3:3.1.1\\\",\\n./stats/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/3.1.1/execution-metrics.json:7:    \\\"previous_library\\\": \\\"org.typelevel:cats-effect_3:2.5.1\\\",\\n./stats/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/3.1.1/execution-metrics.json:83:      \\\"test_file\\\": \\\"tests/src/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/3.1.1/src/test/scala/org_typelevel/cats_effect_3/Cats_effect_3Test.scala\\\",\\n./stats/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/3.1.1/execution-metrics.json:84:      \\\"metadata_file\\\": \\\"metadata/org.typelevel/cats-effect_3/3.1.1/reachability-metadata.json\\\"\\n./stats/org.typelevel/munit-cats-effect_3/2.2.0/execution-metrics.json:4:    \\\"library\\\": \\\"org.typelevel:munit-cats-effect_3:2.2.0\\\",\\n./stats/org.typelevel/munit-cats-effect_3/2.2.0/execution-metrics.json:52:      \\\"test_file\\\": \\\"tests/src/org.typelevel/munit-cats-effect_3/2.2.0/src/test/scala/org